cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on resource allocation in a mobile-edge computing network, which involves wireless communication and networking aspects. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimization problems related to completion time and energy consumption, which can be analyzed using information theory tools. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an iterative algorithm for resource allocation, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with distributed resource allocation in a mobile-edge computing network. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper aims to improve the end-to-end delay of applications in wireless networks, which can be related to multimedia applications.
